<subSubSection id="7482E28FD5B61B86199C63EC06F47AC3" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4BB18E00EF3220D8FE21EC08A98E5451" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9FD48A995C736F20EA3F3F831A5458DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
BL = 20mm. Dorsal side bicolored, pronotum with metallic luster, purple, green, blue or nearly black, elytra black with faint metallic reflections; pronotum lateral margins strongly sinuate in front of posterior angles; posterior angles sharp and base rectangular; basal fovea more or less punctate and rugose; metepisternum long and narrow; apical lamella of aedeagus with rounded apex, shallowly notched or not. 
<taxonomicName id="4B2BFCB715533ADF95C843D7E76AAB6B" authorityName="Brulle" authorityYear="1834" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trigonotoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trigonotoma indica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="38ED0EDFEB53C923D6CA4A15EDD85D78" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Trigonotoma indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be readily distinguished from all other Chinese species by the pronotum lateral margins that are strongly sinuate near base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="438CE66B8609B01B2429C5D9F92D1063" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph id="EB7BE289E12571699CB3D96AC93AFC5F" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Supplementary descriptions on endophallus.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C6877CF3B9AB5456BB25D737658EB55" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName id="3E2A2E0CC15E6C55EE9119CAFA2A5FD7" authorityName="M. Zang &amp; R.H. Petersen" authorityYear="1989" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phallaceae" genus="Endophallus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Endophallus" order="Phallales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Endophallus</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D21E29B00BEAA01414A7DC5BCD7BE9EE" captionStart="Figures 9–12" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 9 - 12. Trigonotoma indica Brulle, 1834. 9 Habitus (male, Xizang, IZAS) 10 labels 11 median lobe of aedeagus A dorsal view B left lateral view 12 endophallus A left lateral view B dorsal view C right lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.921.47258.figures9-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/392469" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">12</figureCitation>
) bent to dorsal direction of aedeagus, major portion of endophallus on dorsal side of aedeagus; gp located at approx middle of aedeagus, oriented to aedeagal base; gpl large, rounded, membranous, bb absent; cp absent. Four distinct lobes recognized: bl moderately large, slightly prolonged, located at base of apical orifice, pointing to apical direction of aedeagus, with a few scales on left side; ll moderately large, divided into several sub-lobes, located at left side of endophallus, with fine scales; rl smaller than ll, rounded, located at right side of endophallus, with fine scales; al large, divided into several sub-lobes, located at apex of endophallus, connected with base of endophallus through a narrow area, forming a dumbbell-shape, with fine scales. Middle of endophallus large, rounded, with a V-shaped sa on left middle and fine scales on apex.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B3840EE5B1501683EDE6E08501BF1283" doi="10.3897/zookeys.921.47258.figures9-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/392469" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" start="Figures 9–12" startId="F3">
