<subSubSection id="A16A5A8C76AB110FB520255D3C9C1907" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="286A5ACC9F84380C8FD35BE488DF6E67" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0FDAF3B568B5DB11C7DD674D1477BECF" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
China (Tibet: 
<normalizedToken id="E5C905A64F505ED592F7F78F919A0E5A" originalValue="Mêdog">Medog</normalizedToken>
), India, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, and Pakistan. Another subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="6F0DBAE7E2F849FF5FA7F584F949A3A6" genus="T." lsidName="T. indica subsp. nepalensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" rank="subSpecies" species="indica" subSpecies="nepalensis">
<emphasis id="56E2BCCA2A4C842FD0F54E0D0ADD0611" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">T. indica nepalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is distributed in Nepal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AE33A9A33C6DB33A71B491BC64A1534" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="83E5CD1A64A907DADE0CCBAFEFE32FE6" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79387D62A5386D978AAF3221B49361E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
It is expected this species would be found to be widely distributed in and around China. Identification is based on the comparison of the image of holotype (
<bibRefCitation id="6169701DAE38AD4434D0632FE094DBE8" author="Roux, P" journalOrPublisher="Roux, France" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" refId="B24" refString="Roux, P, Lassalle, B, Dubault, G, 2016. Les Trigonotomi. Revision. B. Lassalle et P. Roux, France" title="Les Trigonotomi. Revision. B. Lassalle et P." year="2016">Roux et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and specimens from Andhra Prad., India. Compared with the specimens from India, 
<taxonomicName id="1CF074A88789146CB1B1CD6E054AFEB3" genus="T." lsidName="T. indica" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="2BE73DC65D5CCE43F427E3BA83895592" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">T. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken id="6382608CD58FD89290ECEA36081063A0" originalValue="Mêdog">Medog</normalizedToken>
is slightly larger and more vividly green on its pronotum.
</paragraph>
